(19, 'UG', 1, 'all-india-medical', 'All India Medical Admission Process', './assets/images/AIMAP.jpeg', 'All India Medical Admission Process', 'Medical Courses Admission DetailsMedical Counselling Committee of DGHS in Ministry of Health and Family Welfare, Govt. of India, New Delhi is conducting Online Counselling for allotment of Under Graduate (MBBS/BDS) seats to the eligible and qualified candidates under 15% All India Quota in participating Government Medical/Dental Colleges of the country every year.\n\nThe allotment of seat to the candidates is made based on the NEET-UG Examination conducted by National Testing Agency (NTA). also conducting Online Counselling for allotment of Under Graduate (MBBS/BDS) seats to the eligible and qualified candidates in participating Deemed Universities of the country on the basis of NEET (UG) examination conducted by NTA. Qualified and eligible candidates are required to register on the MCC website i.e. www.mcc.nic.in to participate in the counselling process for allotment of seat. MCC does not allot any seat either on nomination basis or manually.', '\r\n**Eligibility Condition for AIQ**\r\nThe candidate should have qualified NEET UG.\r\nDomicile is not required.\r\nEligibility as per norms of NMC.\r\n\r\n**Eligibility Condition for Deemed University**\r\nThe candidate should have qualified NEET UG.\r\nDomicile is not required.\r\n\r\n**Eligibility Condition for AIIMS**\r\nThe candidate should have qualified NEET UG.\r\nDomicile is not required.\r\nEligibility conditions as per AIIMS will be applicable.\r\n\r\n**Eligibility Condition for Insured Person Quota candidates of ESIC**\r\nThe candidate should have a Ward of Insured Persons certificate with a distinct number.\r\nThe candidate should have qualified the All India Examination, i.e., NEET UG, for the relevant year.\r\nDomicile is not required.\r\nReservation for MBBS/BDS seats under Insured Persons’ Quota will be as per the extant Government of India guidelines.\r\n\r\n**Eligibility Condition for DU Internal Quota**\r\nThe eligibility conditions are provided by DU Authority for State Quota admission to MBBS/BDS courses.\r\n\r\n**Eligibility condition for VMMC & SJH; ABVIMS & RML; ESIC, Dental State Quota seats**\r\nThe location of the school/college from which the candidates have passed the qualifying examination will determine their region. Candidates who studied 10+2 (11th and 12th) in recognized schools/colleges in Delhi and passed the qualifying examination from any school/college are eligible.\r\n\r\n**Eligibility condition for Internal Quota seats of AMU**\r\nEligibility conditions for AMU Internal candidates are given by AMU Authorities.\r\nCandidates are advised to check the eligibility criteria for internal quota of AMU on the official AMU website.\r\nMCC has no role in deciding the internal eligibility criteria for AMU.\r\n\r\n**Eligibility condition for Banaras Hindu University**\r\nDomicile is not required.\r\nCandidates who have qualified NEET are eligible to apply.\r\n\r\n**Eligibility Condition for JIPMER Internal seats**\r\nThe candidate should have qualified NEET UG.\r\nCandidates are advised to go through Annexure-10 for eligibility quota details, provided by JIPMER Authorities. MCC has no role in this.\r\nThe list of domicile candidates for internal seats is provided by State authorities of Puducherry. MCC has no role in determining the domicile status of candidates. In case of any discrepancy, candidates should approach the State Authorities.\r\n\r\n**Quota Distribution**\r\nAll India Government Colleges (MBBS/BDS) – 15%\r\nBanaras Hindu University (MBBS/BDS) – 100%\r\nAIIMS (MBBS) – 100%\r\nJIPMER – 100%\r\nAligarh Muslim University – 100%\r\nJamia (BDS) – 100%\r\nESIC – 15%\r\nDeemed University – 100%\r\n', 'Reservation Policy\r\nCategory	Reservation Percentage\r\nScheduled Caste	15%\r\nSchedule Tribe (ST)	7.5%\r\nOther Backward Classes (OBC)	27%\r\nEWS	10%\r\nPerson with Disability (PwD)	5%', 'Fee Structure\r\n\r\nFor Normal University\r\nNon Refundable Fee Structure	Rs. 1000/-	for UR/EWS candidates\r\nRs. 500/-	For SC/ ST/ OBC/ PwD candidates\r\nRefundable security amount (to be refunded only in the account from which payment has been made).	Rs.10,000/-	for UR/EWS candidates\r\nRs. 5,000/-	For SC/ ST/ OBC/ PwD candidates\r\n\r\nFor Deemed University\r\nNon Refundable Registration Fee	Rs. 5000/- (same for all candidates)\r\nRefundable Security amount (to be refunded only in the account from which payment has been made)	Rs. 2,00,000/-\r\n\r\n*Any candidate opting for Deemed University will have to pay Rs 5000/- Non Refundable fee + Rs 2,00,000/- Refundable security amount at the time of the Registration.\r\n\r\n\r\nFor (15% All India Quota)/ Central Universities (DU, AMU, BHU and Jamia Millia Islamia, Delhi)/AFMC& ESI/ All AIIMS/ JIPMER/B.Sc. Nursing\r\n\r\n\r\nAny UR candidate opting for Central Universities/ AFMC/ ESI will pay Rs. 1000/-+ Rs. 10,000= Rs. 11,000 at the time of registration\r\n\r\nAny SC/ST/OBC/PwD candidate will pay Rs. 500 + Rs.5,000 = Rs. 5,500 at the time of registration\r\n\r\nThe Security Deposit will be forfeited if a candidate who has been allotted a seat in the Second Round or subsequent rounds and does not join the respective institution. Also, the Security Deposit will be forfeited if the admission gets cancelled due to any reason', 'Process Flow\r\nRound 1\r\nCandidates who registered for Round-1 and did not get any seat allotted are not required to register again. Also, candidates who have not reported in Round-1, need not register again\r\n\r\nFresh New Registration for Round-2 for those candidates who have not registered in Round-1 (with full payment of fees)\r\n\r\nExercising of “Fresh Choice filling” and Locking of choices\r\n\r\nProcess of Seat Allotment Round-2\r\n\r\nPublication of result of Round-2 on MCC website\r\n\r\nUploading of essential certificates after declaration of result\r\n\r\nPhysical Reporting with original documents at the allotted Medical/Dental College against 2nd Round - (Candidates who have allotted a seat in round 2 can opt for willingness to upgrade from round 2 to round 3 for which they will have to physically report at the allotted college.)\r\n\r\nIf upgraded in Round 2, the candidate must take relieving from Round 1 seat and join Round 2 seat\r\n\r\nCandidates allotted seats in round 2 but who don\'t report or join the allotted institute shall forfeit their security deposit\r\n\r\nCandidates allotted seats in round 2 but who don\'t report or join the allotted institute shall forfeit their security deposit\r\n\r\n\r\nRound 3\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nCandidates who registered for Round 1 or Round 2 and did not get any seat allotted are not required to register again\r\n\r\nFresh New Registration Round 3 for those candidates who 1) Have not registered in Round-1 or Round 2 (with full payment of fees). 2) Have Resigned / Not reported in Round-1 or Round 2 need to fill fresh choices only with full payment of fees\r\n\r\nExercising of “Fresh Choice filling” and Locking of choices\r\n\r\nProcess of Seat Allotment Round-3\r\n\r\nPublication of result of Round 3 on MCC website\r\n\r\nUploading of essential certificates after declaration of result\r\n\r\nPhysical Reporting with original documents at the allotted Medical/Dental College against Round 3 allotted seat\r\nIf upgraded, the candidate must take relieving from Round 2 seat and join Round 3 seat. Once joined, he cannot upgrade or resign from this seat\r\nIf allotted a seat, the candidate cannot upgrade or resign. If any candidate does not join Round 3 seat, he may exit with forfeiture of fess and elimination (cannot participate in any further rounds)\r\n\r\n\r\nFinal Stray Vacancy Round\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nFresh registrations shall be done for Final Stray Vacancy Round\r\n\r\nData will be shared with Centre and the States after Round 3 and if any candidate has his name in the list of allotted candidates in either Centre or State, then such candidates shall be eliminated from the All India Stray Vacancy Round\r\n\r\nAIQ Stray Vacancy Round for vacant seats of Round 3 and Deemed University seats will be conducted by MCC of DGHS, MoHFW through online mode\r\n', 'FAQ\r\nIs there any restriction for filling up number of choices of Institution (College) (and courses i.e. MBBS, BDS and B.Sc. Nursing) in choice filling form?\r\nNo, you can give as many choices as you wish during online choice filling.\r\n\r\nIf a candidate does not report at the allotted college during Round 2 whether he has to register again for Round 3?\r\nYes, Candidate security amount will be forfeited and he can participate in Round 3 only with Fresh Payment.\r\n\r\nWho are eligible for 2nd Round of allotment?\r\nCandidates eligible for seat allotment in 2nd round would be from one of the following groups:\r\n\r\nGroup I: Registered candidates who did not get any seat allotment in the 1st round.\r\n\r\nGroup II: Registered candidates who have secured seat & whose 1st round of allotted seat got cancelled during the document verification on reporting for admission will be considered for allotment of seat in the next round of seat allotment, with changed Category, subject to availability of seat in respective category.\r\n\r\nGroup III: Candidates who have reported at allotted institute during 1st round of allotment and submitted willingness for second round up-gradation as Yes.\r\n\r\nGroup IV: Candidates who have been allotted a seat but Not Joined.\r\n\r\nGroup V: Candidates who have resigned in online mode during the time frame from the allotted seat of first round at college.\r\n\r\nWho are eligible for 3rd Round of allotment?\r\nCandidates eligible for seat allotment in 3rd round would be from one of the following groups\r\n\r\nGroup I: Registered candidates who did not get any seat allotment in the Round 1 or Round 2.\r\n\r\nGroup II: Registered candidates who have secured seat & whose 2nd round of allotted seat got cancelled during the document verification on reporting for admission will be considered for allotment of seat in the next round of seat allotment, with changed Category, subject to availability of seat in respective category.\r\n\r\nGroup III: Candidates who have reported at allotted institute during 2nd round of allotment and submitted willingness for third round up-gradation as Yes.\r\n\r\nGroup IV: Candidates who have been allotted a seat in Round 2 but did not join or resign and exited after forfeiture of fees.\r\n\r\nCan I modify my choices during the period of “Exercising of Choices and Locking” (during first round) and “Fresh Choice submission and locking for 2nd Round and subsequent rounds\r\nYes, you can modify, add or delete your choices during this period, before you lock your choices. But once you lock your Choices then you cannot modify.\r\n\r\nWho are not eligible for Stray Vacancy Round of AIQ/Deemed/ Central Universities/ AIIMS/JIPMER?\r\nFollowing categories of Candidates are not eligible for Stray Vacancy Round:- a) Candidates who have not registered for Stray Vacancy Round. b) Candidate joined/holding any seat at the time of Stray Vacancy Round. c) Candidates allotted a seat in Round 3 of MCC and NOT REPORTED. All candidates not falling under above-mentioned categories are eligible.\r\n\r\nWill there be any Fresh Registration/choice filling for Stray Vacancy Round?\r\nYes, there will be Fresh Registration/choice filling for Stray vacancy Round.\r\n\r\nIn case candidate had to apply for both Govt. Medical/Dental/Nursing and for Deemed University should the candidate pay the fee for both?\r\nNo. As per the policy, the candidate has to pay only the higher fee. In this case the candidate will have to pay fee for Deemed University i.e. Rs. 5000/- (counseling/registration) plus Rs. 2,00,000/- (security amount).\r\n\r\nWhen and where this Security Deposit will be refunded?\r\nSecurity amount will be refunded only after the completion of all rounds of Counseling. MCC will notify about the completion counselling on their portal “www.mcc.nic.in”. The Financial Custodian will initiate the refund of security deposit within 15 days of such notification and complete within 30 days of such notification.', '\r\nIntroduction\r\nMedical Counselling Committee (MCC) of DGHS, Ministry of Health and Family Welfare, Govt. of India, New Delhi conducts online counselling for allotment of Under Graduate (MBBS/BDS) seats under 15% All India Quota in participating Government Medical/Dental Colleges and in Deemed Universities based on NEET-UG examination conducted by NTA. Qualified candidates must register on the MCC website (www.mcc.nic.in) to participate. MCC does not allot any seat manually or on nomination basis.\r\n\r\nEligibility\r\nEligibility Condition for AIQ:\r\n- Candidate should have qualified NEET UG\r\n- Domicile free\r\n- As per norms of NMC\r\n\r\nEligibility Condition for Deemed University:\r\n- Candidate should have qualified NEET UG\r\n- Domicile free\r\n\r\nEligibility Condition for AIIMS:\r\n- Candidate should have qualified NEET UG\r\n- Domicile free\r\n- Eligibility conditions as per AIIMS\r\n\r\nEligibility Condition for ESIC (Insured Person Quota):\r\n- Candidate should have Ward of Insured Persons certificate with distinct number\r\n- Candidate should have qualified NEET UG\r\n- Domicile free\r\n- Reservation as per Govt. of India guidelines\r\n\r\nEligibility for DU Internal Quota, VMMC & SJH, ABVIMS & RML, ESIC Dental State Quota, AMU Internal, BHU, JIPMER Internal: As provided by respective authorities. MCC has no role in internal quota eligibility.\r\n\r\nQuota Distribution:\r\nColleges                        Quota\r\nAll India Government Colleges   15%\r\nBanaras Hindu University        100%\r\nAIIMS (MBBS)                    100%\r\nJIPMER                          100%\r\nAligarh Muslim University       100%\r\nJamia (BDS)                     100%\r\nESIC                            15%\r\nDeemed University               100%\r\n\r\nReservation Policy:\r\nCategory                     Percentage\r\nScheduled Caste (SC)         15%\r\nScheduled Tribe (ST)          7.5%\r\nOther Backward Classes (OBC) 27%\r\nEconomically Weaker Section (EWS) 10%\r\nPerson with Disability (PwD)  5%\r\nNo reservation for Deemed Universities.\r\n\r\nFee Structure:\r\nNormal University:\r\n- Non-refundable: UR/EWS Rs. 1000, SC/ST/OBC/PwD Rs. 500\r\n- Refundable Security: UR/EWS Rs. 10,000, SC/ST/OBC/PwD Rs. 5,000\r\n\r\nDeemed University:\r\n- Non-refundable Registration Fee Rs. 5000 (all candidates)\r\n- Refundable Security Amount Rs. 2,00,000\r\n\r\nProcess Flow:\r\nRound 1:\r\n- Candidates registered for Round 1 not allotted seat need not register again\r\n- Fresh registration for Round 2 for new candidates\r\n- Choice filling and locking\r\n- Seat allotment and result publication on MCC website\r\n- Upload essential certificates and physical reporting\r\n- Upgradation rules and security forfeiture if not joined\r\n\r\nRound 3:\r\n- Similar process as Round 2 with fresh registration for eligible candidates\r\n- Reporting rules and security forfeiture if not joined\r\n\r\nFinal Stray Vacancy Round:\r\n- Fresh registrations for vacant seats\r\n- AIQ Stray Vacancy Round conducted online by MCC\r\n\r\nFAQ:\r\n- Candidates can give unlimited choices during online choice filling\r\n- Security amount forfeited if candidate does not report and must pay fresh fees for next round\r\n- Eligibility for 2nd and 3rd round defined by registration and seat allotment status\r\n- Choice modification allowed before locking\r\n- Not eligible for Stray Vacancy Round if already holding/occupied seat or not registered\r\n- Security deposit refunded after all rounds, processed within 30 days\r\n\r\nCounselling Centres:\r\n- State-wise centres are designated for candidate convenience\r\n- Candidates select preferred centre during registration\r\n- Details (address/contact) notified on MCC portal www.mcc.nic.in\r\n', 1, 1, '2026-01-07 10:37:02', '2026-01-09 05:48:11'),
(28, 'UG', 1, 'maharashtra-medical', 'Maharashtra Medical Admission Process', './assets/images/MMAP.jpeg', 'Maharashtra Medical Admission Process', 'The Counselling for all admission to MBBS/BDS/BAMS/BHMS/BUMS/BPTh/ BOTh/BASLP/BP&O Course in all Health Science Educational Institutions in a State/Union territory, including Health Science Educational Institutions established by the Central Government, State Government, University, Trust, Society/Minority Institutions/Corporations or a Company shall be conducted by the State/Union Territory Government. Such common counselling shall be under the over-all superintendence, direction and control of the State/Union Territory Government.\r\n\r\nThere shall be a single eligibility cum entrance examination namely ‘National Eligibility-cum-Entrance Test for admission to all Health Science courses’ for academic year 2024-25. it shall be necessary for a candidate to obtain minimum marks in ‘National Eligibility-cum-Entrance Test’ held for the said academic year, besides obtaining minimum prescribed marks at the qualifying examination as prescribed by respective central council.\r\n\r\nAll admissions to Health Science courses within the respective categories shall be based solely on merit (AIR) in the National Eligibility-cum-Entrance Test. National Testing Agency shall be the organization to conduct National Eligibility- cum-Entrance Test for admission to MBBS/BDS/BAMS/BUMS/BHMS courses. Accordingly, the National Testing Agency, Delhi conducted the National EligibilitY Cum Entrance Test for the session 2024-25.\r\n\r\n15% seats in Government, Corporation and Govt.-Aided Medical and Dental Colleges of Maharashtra will be filled by Directorate General of Health Services, New Delhi (DGHS) And 15% seats in Government / Govt.-Aided & Unaided Private/Minority Colleges of AYUSH courses in Maharashtra will be filled by AACCC on the basis of All India NEET Rank.\r\n\r\nThe Competent Authority shall issue Notice regarding schedule of online registration and submission of online Application from eligible candidates for the preparation of provisional state merit list for admission to undergraduate courses for all seats available with The Competent Authority in State of Maharashtra.', 'Eligibility\r\nEligibility For Admission To Health Science Degree Course\r\n\r\n•\r\nThe candidate must be an Indian National\r\n•\r\nThe candidate must be registered with State CET cell, Mumbai through online application on website of State CET Cell\r\n•\r\nDomicile of Candidate: The Candidates must be Domicile of Maharashtra\r\n•\r\nThe candidate must have passed the SSC or equivalent examination from an Institution situated in the state of Maharashtra\r\n•\r\nThe candidate must have passed the qualifying examination i.e. Higher Secondary\r\n•\r\nCertificate (HSC/12th Standard) or equivalent examination, from an Institution situated in the State of Maharashtra exception) with English, Physics, Chemistry and Biology (Botany & Zoology) at the time of document verification\r\n\r\nEligibility criteria of Qualifying Examination for various courses\r\n\r\n', 'For MBBS/BDS/BAMS/BUMS/BHMS\r\n\r\nOPEN Category and EWS Category	Category must have obtained not less than 50% marks in Physics, Chemistry and Biology taken together at the HSC\r\nconstitutional reservation and constitutional reservation with PWD	Must have obtained not less than 40% (i.e. 120 out of 300) marks in Physics, Chemistry and Biology taken together at the HSC (or equivalent) Examination\r\n\r\n\r\nFor BPTh, BOTh, BASLP & BP & O CourseS\r\n\r\nPassing grade at HSC/12th Standard or equivalent examination is however necessary\r\n\r\nFor admission to BP&O\r\n\r\nCandidates who have passed 12th standard examination with Physics, Chemistry, Biology and / or Mathematics are eligible\r\n\r\nFor admission to BASLP\r\n\r\nCandidates who have passed 12th standard examination with Physics, Biology, Chemistry and/or Mathematics and/or Computer Science are eligible', 'Fee Structure\r\n\r\nName of the Course	Candidate seeking admission for State Quota Seats	Candidate seeking admission for Institute Quota Seats	Candidate seeking admission for both State Quota and Institute Quota\r\nMBBS, BDS, BAMS, BHMS & BUMS	Rs. 1000/-	Rs. 5000/-	Rs. 6000/-\r\nBPTH, BOTH, BASLP & BP&O	Rs. 1000/-	Rs. 1000/-	Rs. 1000/-\r\n', 'Process Flow\r\nFlowchart\r\n\r\n\r\n•\r\nOnline registration\r\n•\r\nApplication form filling\r\n•\r\nPayment of registration fees\r\n•\r\nUploading of Documents\r\n•\r\nPublication of State Merit list\r\n\r\n\r\nRound 1\r\n\r\n\r\n•\r\nOnline preferences(choices) filling process for first round\r\n•\r\nDeclaration of the list of selected candidates of the first round\r\n•\r\nLast date of joining to the respective college for the first round\r\n\r\n\r\nRound 2\r\n\r\n\r\n•\r\nOnline preferences(choices) filling process for second round\r\n•\r\nDeclaration of the list of selected candidates of the second round\r\n•\r\nLast date of joining to the respective college for the second round\r\n\r\n\r\nRound 3\r\n\r\n\r\n•\r\nOnline registration, application form filling, payment of registration fees and uploading of Documents for Round 3 (if not registered previously)\r\n•\r\nPublication of Combined State Merit list (Round 1 &Round 3 )\r\n•\r\nOnline preferences(choices) filling process for Round 3\r\n•\r\nDeclaration of the list of selected candidate for Round 3\r\n•\r\nLast date of joining to the respective colleges for Round 3\r\n\r\n\r\nOnline Stray Vacancy round(s)\r\n\r\n\r\n•\r\nCut-off-date of admission process for MBBS\r\n•\r\nCut-off-date of admission process for BDS\r\n', 'FAQ\r\nCan I Do MBBS Without NEET ?\r\nNo, it\'s not possible to do MBBS without NEET. Candidates must have to appear for the NEET exam for admissions. However, there are only a few private colleges in India that offer direct MBBS admissions or through any other entrance test.\r\n\r\nWhat is the age limit for NEET?\r\nThe age limit for NEET is 17 years. Candidates appearing for the NEET exam must be older than 17 years while registering for the NEET exam.\r\n\r\nHow many government MBBS seats are available in Maharashtra?\r\nThere are 4825 Government MBBS Seats Availible in Maharashtra\r\n\r\nWhat is required to satisfy eligibility criteria as far as only 12th Std. is concerned? Is it 50% marks in PCB or 50% in PCBE or 50% in grand total?\r\nGeneral category: A candidate must have passed in the subjects of Physics, Chemistry, Biology/Bio-technology and English individually and must have obtained a minimum of 50% marks taken together in Physics, Chemistry, Biology/Biotechnology at the Qualifying Examination.\r\n\r\nSC, ST and OBC-NCL category: The marks obtained in Physics, Chemistry, Biology/Biotechnology taken in qualifying examination must be 40% marks.\r\n\r\nFor candidates with Benchmark Disabilities: the minimum marks in qualifying examination in Physics, Chemistry and Biology/Biotechnology taken together must be 45%.\r\n\r\nIs there any restriction for filling up number of choices of Institution (College) in choice filling form?\r\nNo, you can give as many choices as you wish during online choice filling.\r\n\r\nWhat Documents Are Required For Admission process?\r\n\r\nAdmit card of NEET UG 2023\r\n\r\nCopy of Online Application Form (Latest) filled on www.mahacet.org\r\n\r\nNEET-UG 2023 Mark sheet\r\n\r\nNationality certificate issued by District Magistrate/Addl. District Magistrate or Metropolitan Magistrate / valid Indian passport /School Leaving Certificate of HSC/12th Std. indicating the nationality of the candidate as Indian\r\nDomicile Certificate issued by District Magistrate/Metropolitan Magistrate/ Addl. District Magistrate or Competent Authority for issue of such certificate\r\n\r\nH.S.C. (or equivalent) examination marksheet\r\n\r\nSSC (or equivalent) passing certificate (for Date of Birth)\r\n\r\nAadhar Card\r\n\r\nMedical fitness certificate (Annexure - H)\r\n\r\nIf Applicable :\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nCaste Certificate\r\n\r\nCaste Validity Certificate\r\n\r\nNon Creamy layer Certificate valid upto 31/03/2025 (For DT-A, NT-B, NT-C, NT-D& OBC including SBC)\r\n\r\nEx-servicemen Certificate /actual service certificate\r\n\r\nDomicile of Maharashtra Certificate of Defence person\r\n\r\nTransfer certificate and Domicile of other than Maharashtra certificate of parents\r\n\r\nEligibility Certificate for EWS category issued by appropriate authority, for the year 2024-25\r\n\r\nMKB: Disputed area certificate, Mother tongue certificate, SSC/HSC from MKB area\r\n\r\nHA: Parent Domicile certificate, SSC/HSC of candidate from hilly area\r\n\r\nFor Person with disability (PWD) Candidates - Medical Fitness Certificate of Authorized Medical Board\r\n\r\nFor Minority Candidates - Refer rule 5.11, 5.12 & 5.13\r\n\r\nFor Orphan - respective certificate from Women and Child welfare department\r\nWhich Candidates are eligible for seat allotment in Round 2 ? Que -Which Candidates are eligible for seat allotment in Round 2 ?\r\n\r\nRegistered candidates who did not fill choices in Round 1\r\n\r\nRegistered candidates who participated in Round1 but did not get any seat allotted in Round 1\r\n\r\nRegistered candidates, whose seat allotted in Round 1 got cancelled during the document verification\r\n\r\nCandidates who have reported/joined at allotted institute during the joining period of Round1 of allotment and did not filled Status Retention Form\r\n\r\nCandidate who does not join the allotted seat during Round1\r\n\r\nCandidate who has joined and resigned upto the last date of joining Round 1\r\nCandidate who has joined and resigned upto the last date of joining Round 1.\r\n\r\nRegistered candidates who did not fill choices in Round1 & Round 2\r\n\r\nCandidates who are joined in Round 2 but did not filled Status Rentension Form\r\n\r\nRegistered candidates who participated in Round1 & Round2 but did not get any seat allotted in Round1 & Round2\r\n\r\nCandidates who have registered in Round 3\r\nEligible Which Candidates Are Eligible For Online CAP Stray Vacancy Round ?\r\nCandidate who have registered & filled online preference form previously but not been allotted a seat till Round 3.', NULL, 2, 1, '2026-01-07 10:39:14', '2026-01-09 06:38:38'),
(29, 'UG', 1, 'karnataka-medical', 'Karnataka Medical Admission Process', './assets/images/KMAP.jpeg', 'Karnataka Medical Admission Process', 'The Karnataka Medical Admission Process for NEET PG is managed by the Karnataka Examinations Authority (KEA). This process ensures fair and transparent allocation of postgraduate medical seats in government and private medical colleges across Karnataka. Eligible candidates must qualify the NEET PG exam, complete online registration, document verification, and participate in counselling rounds to secure admission. The process follows a merit-based system with category reservation, application fees, and a defined seat allotment procedure.', 'Candidate must be an Indian citizen.\r\n\r\nMust possess a recognized MBBS degree from a medical college approved by the National Medical Commission (NMC).\r\n\r\nCompletion of a one-year internship by the date specified by KEA.\r\n\r\nMust have a valid NEET PG score.\r\n\r\nMust be registered with NMC or any State Medical Council.\r\n\r\nCandidates must meet the minimum marks and category-wise requirements as specified by KEA.\r\n\r\nCandidates who have already completed or are pursuing postgraduate studies may be eligible under specific rules (check KEA notifications).', 'Category-wise reservation (State quota, 85% seats)\r\n\r\nSC (Scheduled Caste)     15%\r\n\r\nST (Scheduled Tribe)      3%\r\n\r\nOBC (Other Backward Classes – including Karnataka state OBC)      27%\r\n\r\nEWS (Economically Weaker Section)   10%\r\n\r\nGeneral Category (Unreserved) Remaining seats\r\n\r\nHorizontal Reservations\r\nPersons with Disability (PWD)     5%\r\n\r\nWomen candidates As per applicable state rules.\r\n\r\nAll India Quota (15% seats in government colleges)\r\n\r\nSeats are filled through central counselling conducted by MCC, following NEET PG rank.\r\n\r\nNRI / Foreign / Management quota\r\n\r\nSeparate seats with different fee structures.', 'Application/Registration Fee \r\n General  ₹1,500\r\n SC/ST   ₹750\r\n NRI/Foreign   As per KEA\r\n\r\nTuition Fee: \r\nGovernment     ₹50,000 – ₹2,00,000 per year\r\n Private     ₹5 – 15 Lakhs per year\r\n\r\nSecurity Deposit / Bond\r\n\r\nRefundable security deposit may apply; penalties for leaving mid-course', '1. Candidates can apply “online” only for Karnataka State UG NEET-2023.\r\n2. Information Bulletin can be downloaded from the Website http://kea.kar.nic.in\r\n3. Online submission of Application Form may be made by accessing KEA Website\r\nhttp://kea.kar.nic.in\r\n4. Candidates must follow the instructions strictly as given in the Information Bulletin and on KEA\r\nWebsite http://kea.kar.nic.in. Candidates not complying with the instructions will be summarily\r\ndisqualified.\r\n5. Candidates must retain the following documents with them as reference for future\r\ncorrespondence.\r\n(i) At least two printouts of the finally submitted online Application.\r\n(ii) UGNEET-2023 Admit Card and UGNEET-2023 Score Card.\r\n(iii) 2 passport size identical photograph which is uploaded in the Online Application.\r\n6. Registered Mobile Number\r\n(i) Candidate must ensure that mobile numbers, e-mail address entered in the online\r\napplication form are his/her own as in case of urgency KEA may send information /\r\ncommunications by SMS or email on registered mobile number and registered\r\nemail ID only.\r\n(ii) KEA will not be held responsible for non-receipt of latest information due to wrong\r\nmobile number or mailing address filled in the Online Application Form.\r\n7. Candidates must preserve the UG NEET 2023 Admit Card and UGNEET-2023 Score Card till the\r\nadmission in College or Institution.\r\n8. For the latest updates, candidates must remain in touch with the KEA Website\r\nhttp://kea.kar.nic.in till the completion of all rounds of counseling.\r\n9. Candidates / parents are advised to visit KEA Website http://kea.kar.nic.in at least twice in a\r\nday for the latest news / updates and also check their mobile / e-mail as in case of urgency KEA\r\nmay send the information / communications.\r\n10. KEA will reserve the right to withdraw any such admission made at any point of time which is\r\nnot fulfill', 'Who conducts the MBBS/BDS admission counselling in Karnataka?\r\nMBBS/BDS counselling in Karnataka is conducted by the Karnataka Examinations Authority (KEA)for state quota seats, while 15% All India Quota (AIQ)  counselling is handled separately by the Medical Counselling Committee (MCC). ([Jagranjosh.com][1])\r\n\r\nWhat exam score is required to participate?\r\nEligibility for Karnataka MBBS/BDS admission is based on qualifying NEET‑UG 2025 score and meeting the minimum percentile — candidates must have passed Physics, Chemistry, Biology & English in 12th standard. ([Collegedunia][2])\r\n\r\nHow do I register for Karnataka MBBS counselling?\r\nEligible candidates must register on the official KEA portal (cetonline.karnataka.gov.in/kea), fill in personal and NEET details, upload required documents, and pay the counselling fee online. ([MBBS Admission Abroad.in][3])\r\n\r\nWhat are the main steps in the counselling process?\r\nThe typical process includes:\r\n\r\n1.Registration & document upload**\r\n2.Choice filling and locking of preferred colleges/courses\r\n3.Seat allotment based on rank and choices.\r\n4.Reporting to allotted institute with original documents\r\n5.Further rounds if seat not allotted** (Round 2, Mop‑Up, Stray Vacancy). ([Jagranjosh.com][1])\r\n\r\nHow many rounds of counselling are usually held?\r\nThere are usually multiple rounds: Round 1, Round 2, Mop‑Up Round, and if seats remain vacant, a Stray Vacancy Round is conducted. ([Select Your University][4])\r\n\r\n Can I modify my college choices after filling them?\r\nYes, you can modify, add or delete preference choices before you lock them during the choice filling window. Once locked, choices cannot be changed. ([Jagranjosh.com][1])\r\n\r\nWhat happens after seat allotment?\r\nAfter allotment, candidates must report to the allotted college within the specified time with original documents and pay the fees to confirm admission. ([Jagranjosh.com][1])\r\n\r\nWhat documents are generally required for verification?\r\nDocuments typically include NEET UG scorecard, admit card, 10th & 12th mark sheets, identity proof, study/domicile certificates, caste/income certificates (if applicable), and proof of payment. ([Select Your University][4])\r\n\r\nDo I need to register separately for state quota and AIQ?\r\n Yes. State quota counselling by KEA and AIQ counselling by MCC require **separate registrations on respective official portals. ([Select Your University][4])\r\n\r\nIs there a fee for counselling registration?\r\nYes, counselling registration attracts a fee which varies by category — generally higher for NRI/foreign candidates and lower for reserved categories. ([Select Your University][4])\r\n', NULL, 3, 1, '2026-01-07 10:39:14', '2026-01-09 06:43:57'),
(30, 'UG', 1, 'all-india-ayush', 'All India Ayush Admission Process', './assets/images/AACCC.jpeg', 'All India Ayush Admission Process', 'Introduction\r\nAyush Admissions Central Counselling Committee (AACCC) of the Ministry of Ayush, Govt. of India, New Delhi, conducts Online Counselling for allotment of AIQ- Undergraduate (BAMS/BSMS BUMS/BHMS) seats of Ayurveda/ Siddha/Unani/ Homoeopathy under Govt. /Govt. Aided/Central Universities/National Institutes/Deemed Universities to the NEET (UG) qualified eligible candidates since 2019. For the academic year 2024-25, the allotment of seats is based on the candidate\'s merit in the NEET (UG)- 2024 Examination conducted by the National Testing Agency (NTA).', 'Eligibility\r\nQuota Distribution\r\nColleges	Quota\r\nAll India Quota UG (BAMS/BSMS/BUMS/BHMS) Seats of Govt./Govt. Aided Institute of all States/UTs	15%\r\nBAMS Seats of BHU, Varanasi, Uttar Pradesh	100%\r\nBAMS Seats of ITRA, Jamnagar, Gujarat (except nominated seats)	100%\r\nBAMS seats of NIA, Jaipur, Rajasthan (except nominated seats)	100%\r\nBHMS seats of NIH, Kolkata, West Bengal (except nominated seats)	100%\r\nUG (BAMS/BSMS/BUMS/BHMS) Seats of all Deemed Universities	100%\r\nBAMS seats of AIIA, Goa	50%\r\nBSMS seats of NIS, Chennai	50%\r\nBUMS seats of AMU, Aligarh, Uttar Pradesh	50%\r\nBAMS & BHMS seats of NEIA&H, Shillong, Meghalaya	50%\r\n\r\n\r\nThe above percentage of All India Quota seats is tentative; the number of participating institutes/colleges available in each round of AACCC-UG counselling depends upon permission issued by NCISM/NCH/Concerned University.', 'Reservation Policy\r\nCategory	Reservation Percentage\r\nScheduled Caste	15%\r\nSchedule Tribe (ST)	7.5%\r\nOther Backward Classes (NCL)	27%\r\nEWS	10%\r\nPerson with Disability (PwD)	5%\r\n\r\nCandidates with at least 40% impairment, irrespective of the type of disability, i.e., locomotor, visual or SEVERE dyslexic, shall be eligible for the benefits of the PwBD category. Further, Leprosy-cured candidates who are otherwise fit to pursue the courses also included in this category.\r\n\r\n\r\nAll UG seats of Deemed Universities are domicile free and un-reserved, i.e. reservation policy of Central Govt. is not applicable.', 'Fee Structure\r\n\r\nNon-Refundable Registration Fee\r\nAdmission Type	Category	Amount\r\nAIQ-Govt.-college/AIQ-Govt.Aided-college/ Central University/National Institute	UR/EWS/OBC-NCL candidates	Rs. 1000/-\r\nSC/ ST/ PwBD candidates	Rs. 500/-\r\nDeemed University	All Categories	Rs. 5000/-\r\n\r\nRefundable Security Fee\r\nAdmission Type	Category	Amount\r\nAIQ-Govt.-college/AIQ- Govt. Aided-college/Central University/National Institute	All Categories	Rs. 10000/-\r\nDeemed University	All Categories	Rs. 50000/-\r\n\r\n*Refundable Security Fee will be refunded to candidates after joining the allotted college in the stipulated time mentioned in the schedule or if candidate did not get any seat during all rounds counselling, to the bank account provided by the candidate at the time of registration for AACCC-UG counselling.', 'Process Flow\r\nRound 1\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nRegister on - www.aaccc.gov.in\r\n\r\nPayment By Credit Card/Debit Card/ Net Banking\r\n\r\nAfter Successful Payment Candidate Need To Fill Choices\r\n\r\nChoice Locking\r\n\r\nFirst Round Allotment\r\n\r\nPhysical Reporting To College With Documents And D.D Of Fees\r\n\r\n\r\nRound 2\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nRegistration for AACCC-UG Counseling. (The candidates who participated in 1st Round need not be registered again)\r\n\r\nPayment of Counselling Fee includes Non-Refundable Registration Fee + Security Money (Need not to pay by the candidates, those who already paid the counselling fee at the time of registration for 1st Round.)\r\n\r\nChoice filling and locking\r\nPublication of Seat allotment list (Publication of Result)\r\n\r\nPhysical Reporting to the allotted college\r\n\r\n\r\nRound 3\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nRegistration for AACCC-UG Counseling. (Those candidates who participated in 1st Round/2nd Round need not be registered again)\r\nPayment of Counselling Fee includes non-refundable Registration Fee and Security Money. (No Need to pay by those candidates who have already paid the counselling fee at the time of registration for 1 /2nd Round)\r\n\r\nChoice filling and locking\r\n\r\nPublication of Seat allotment list (Publication of Result)\r\n\r\nPhysical Reporting to the allotted college\r\n\r\n\r\nImportant\r\n\r\n\r\nIt is mandatory for all candidates to take admission on their upgraded seats in the 3 rd Round from Round 1 & 2 admitted seats. Such candidates, if not joined in the upgraded seats, are ineligible for any further AYUSH counseling (Central/State/UT/ Central Pool Quota) and their security money will be forfeited.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nStray Vacancy Round For AIQG/AIQGA/CU/NI\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nThe seats remain vacant (not joined/withdrawn) after the 3rd Round of AACCC-UG Counselling of Govt./Govt. Aided colleges/CU/NI will continue to be filled through the online Stray Vacancy Round conducted by the AACCC, M/o Ayush.\r\n\r\nAll registered candidates who have not been admitted to any of the seats through AACCC-UG counseling or counseling conducted by State/UTs are eligible for Stray Vacancy Round.\r\n\r\n\r\nProcess\r\n\r\nThere is no Fresh Registration in Stray Vacancy Round.\r\n\r\nCandidates must submit a willingness in the AACCC-UG portal to participate in the Stray Vacancy Round with an undertaking that they are not holding any UG (ASU&H) seats allotted through AACCC-UG counseling or counseling conducted by State/UTs.\r\n\r\nOption for choice filling is available in the Stray Vacancy Round.\r\n\r\nNo upgradation is available from any of the 3 Rounds to the Stray Vacancy Round.\r\n\r\nStray Vacancy Round For Deemed University\r\n\r\nFor seat allotment under Deemed Universities, the Stray Vacancy Round will be conducted by the respective Deemed Universities at the institute level.\r\n\r\nAACCC, M/o Ayush will send a list of eligible registered candidates Deemed Universities, which is to be exercised strictly in order of merit in the Stray Vacancy Round.\r\n\r\nThe seats are domicile-free, and only registered candidates of AACCC-UG counseling are eligible for admission.', 'FAQ\r\nDo I require any documents to get registered online?\r\nNo documents are required since it is an online allotment (Counseling) process. However, you need to fill up the similar information which you gave at the time of registration for the NEET (UG)-2023 examination on the NTA website. Further, upload a legible scanned copy of the Cancelled Cheque/Bank Passbook/ Bank e-Statement (having account details) during registration.\r\n\r\nIs there any restriction for filling up the number of choices of Institutions and courses?\r\nYou can give as many choices as you wish during online choice filling. However, the candidate must fill in the choices of colleges/courses in the order of his/her preference (higher to lower). There will be a common counselling platform for AIQ-Govt/Govt Aided/National Institutes/Central/ Deemed Universities for filling up choices.\r\n\r\nCan I know the seat which I will likely get at my rank?\r\nYou can have some idea from the following: The details of Course and category wise Opening and Closing rank of admission in ASU&H- UG courses in the previous year, i.e., A.Y-2022-23, uploaded in the “Current Events” section under UG Counselling tab on the AACCC- website (www.aaccc.gov.in) before the start of 1st Round of AACCC-UG Counselling. This will only be indicative, and the admission pattern for the current A.Y may vary as per the availability of UG seats in ASU&H courses.\r\n\r\nIs filling up and locking of choices necessary to get the seat allotted? Or will I be allotted a seat automatically from leftover seats?\r\nAfter online registration, you must fill in the choices of colleges/courses in order of your preference (higher to lower) and lock it before the server time. The submitted/ filled choices can be modified before locking. If candidates do not lock the choices submitted by them, it will be automatically locked as per schedule/ Server time. You will not be allotted any seats if you don\'t fill in choices even after registering in the AACCC portal. Candidates can download/print out the locked choices for future reference.\r\n\r\nCan I modify my choices during the choice submission period for counselling?\r\nYes, you can modify, add or delete your choices during the choice Filling/Locking period. Further, you are requested to do the same before locking the choices by yourself or the System as per schedule/ server time.\r\n\r\nWhat documents are required at the time of Joining/ Reporting in allotted ASU& H College?\r\n\r\nOriginal documents (along with attested photocopies, preferably 02 sets of documents) required at the time of joining in allotted ASU& H College are as below:\r\n\r\n\r\n•\r\nProvisional Allotment Letter generated online from the AACCC portal\r\n•\r\nAdmit Card for the NEET (UG)-2023 Exam issued by NTA\r\n•\r\nNEET (UG)-2023 Result/ Rank letter issued by NTA\r\n•\r\nDate of Birth Certificate (if the10th Standard Certificate does not bear the same)\r\n•\r\nClass 10th Pass Certificate and Marks sheet\r\n•\r\nClass 12th Pass Certificate and Marks sheet\r\n•\r\nEight (8) Passport size photographs. (Same as affixed on the NEET (UG)- 2023/AACCC-UG counseling-2023 online application form)\r\n•\r\nProof of identity (Aadhar/PAN card/Driving License/Voter ID/ Passport)\r\n•\r\nMedical Fitness Certificate\r\n•\r\nTransfer Certificate from the last studied institution\r\n\r\nIf Applicable\r\n\r\n\r\n•\r\nDisability Certificate\r\n•\r\nSC/ST Certificate\r\n•\r\nOBC-NCL certificate\r\n•\r\nEconomically Weaker Section (GEN-EWS) certificate\r\nIs it necessary to submit Domicile Certificate for admission to AIQ-UG seat under ASU & H stream ?\r\nNo, it is not necessary to submit Domicile Certificate for AIQ-UG seats at the time of admission to the allotted institute as the AIQ seats are domicile free, vide Ministry\'s letter dated 26/05/2023.\r\n\r\nI have submitted willingness for up-gradation in the 2nd Round while joining the 1st Round allotted seat. Later changed my decision and wanted to retain the 1st Round allotted seat; how can I avoid change/cancellation of already allotted college/seat?\r\nThe candidate need not fill any fresh choices for the 2nd Round, so the earlier allotted seat (1st Round allotted) will be retained. If the candidate submits fresh choices during Round-2 and in case the seat gets upgraded, the earlier allotted seat in Round-1 will be cancelled, and the candidate must join the Round-2 upgraded seat.\r\n\r\nWho is eligible for the 2nd Round of allotment?\r\nCandidates eligible for seat allotment in the 2nd Round would be from one of the following groups:\r\n\r\nGroup - I: Newly registered candidate for 2nd Round\r\n\r\nGroup - II: Registered candidates who did not get any seats in the 1st Round.\r\n\r\nGroup - III: Candidates who have reported at the allotted institute during the 1st Round and submitted willingness for 2nd Round up-gradation as \'Yes\'.\r\n\r\nGroup - IV: Candidates who have been alloted a seat in 1st Round but not joined/not Reported (i.e. availed \'free exit\')\r\n\r\nGroup - V: Candidates who have resigned from the allotted seat of 1st Round before the commencement of 2nd Round.\r\n\r\nIs it necessary to join the Upgraded/allotted college If my allotted seat in the 1 st Round gets upgraded in the 2nd Round?\r\nYes, In case the candidate is allotted a seat during the 2nd Round of the allotment process, the seat allotted during the 1st Round will automatically be cancelled immediately (i.e., allotted to somebody else), and the candidate should have to join the college/seat allotted during 2nd Round after obtaining online generated relieving letter from the college allotted in the 1st Round.\r\n\r\nIf a candidate does not join the college/seat allotted or upgraded during the 2nd Round, he/she can avail of free exit. Suppose a candidate joins the allotted/upgraded seat in the 2nd Round; in that case, he/she can exit with forfeiture of security money within the stipulated period (i.e., 3 days prior to the commencement of the 3 rd Round). If the candidate fails to do so, he/she will become ineligible for further counseling. (Central /State/UT/Central Pool Quota).\r\n\r\nSeats can also be upgraded in the same college (same course) by change of category (i.e.ST/SC/OBC to UR or PwD to non-PwD); in such a case, the candidate has to take fresh admission on the upgraded seat, as per the procedure.\r\n\r\nWho will be eligible for the 3rd Round of AACCC-UG Counseling?\r\nThe Following categories of candidates are eligible for the 3rd Round:\r\n\r\n\r\n•\r\nCandidates who are registering for the first time.\r\n•\r\nRegistered candidates who have not been allotted any seat in Round 1 & Round 2.\r\n•\r\nAll candidates admitted in Round 1 or Round 2 and opted for up-gradation of their admitted seats (with fresh choice filling).\r\n•\r\nRound 1 admitted Candidates availed of free exit options within the stipulated period and not participated in the 2nd Round\r\n•\r\nCandidate allotted seat in the 2nd Round and availed free exit (not joined/ not reported).\r\n•\r\nCandidate withdraws from the 2nd Round allotted seat, 3 days prior to commencement of the 3rd Round, with forfeiture of Security Money (Need to remit the complete fees again).\r\nWhat will happen if a candidate does not join the 3rd Round allotted institute?\r\nIf a Candidate does not join the 3rd Round allotted/upgraded seat, the candidate\'s admission will be cancelled with Forfeiture of security money. Further, he/she will become ineligible for any other AYUSH counselling. (Central/State/UT/Central Pool Quota).\r\n\r\nWho is Eligible for Stray Vacancy Round?\r\nAll registered candidates who are not holding any seats allotted through previous rounds of AACCC-UG counseling or counseling conducted by State/UTs are eligible for Stray Vacancy Round. However, Candidates are advised to confirm their eligibility conditions before applying.\r\n\r\nIs any Up-gradation allowed from the 3rd Round to the Stray Vacancy Round of the AACCC-UG counselling?\r\nNo, Up-gradation is not allowed from the 3rd Round to the Stray Vacancy Round of the AACCC-UG counselling.\r\n\r\nIf candidate wish to apply for both AIQ and Deemed University, he/she need to pay fee for both?\r\nNo, in such case the candidate has to pay only the higher fee i.e. of Deemed University Rs.5,000/- (Registration fee) plus Rs.50,000/- (security money).\r\n\r\nWhat are the norms for forfeiture of security money during AACCC-UG counselling?\r\nIf the candidate is not eligible for refund of security money due to non-compliance of counselling scheme, the full security money will be forfeited irrespective of the category of seat (e.g. AIQ-Govt or Deemed University) of seat allotted.\r\n\r\nWhen will the Refundable security amount be refunded if I am eligible as per the Refund Policy?\r\nRefund will be initiated only after completion of all rounds of AACCC-UG Counselling.', NULL, 4, 1, '2026-01-07 10:39:14', '2026-01-09 06:45:28');
