(61, 'PG', 1, 'Maharashtra Medical Admission Process(MMAP)', 'Maharashtra Medical Admission Process(MMAP)', './assets/images/AIMAP.jpeg', 'All India Medical Admission Process', 'Introduction\r\nThe Counselling for all admission to MBBS/BDS/BAMS/BHMS/BUMS/BPTh/ BOTh/BASLP/BP&O Course in all Health Science Educational Institutions in a State/Union territory, including Health Science Educational Institutions established by the Central Government, State Government, University, Trust, Society/Minority Institutions/Corporations or a Company shall be conducted by the State/Union Territory Government. Such common counselling shall be under the over-all superintendence, direction and control of the State/Union Territory Government.\r\n\r\nThere shall be a single eligibility cum entrance examination namely ‘National Eligibility-cum-Entrance Test for admission to all Health Science courses’ for academic year 2024-25. it shall be necessary for a candidate to obtain minimum marks in ‘National Eligibility-cum-Entrance Test’ held for the said academic year, besides obtaining minimum prescribed marks at the qualifying examination as prescribed by respective central council.\r\n\r\nAll admissions to Health Science courses within the respective categories shall be based solely on merit (AIR) in the National Eligibility-cum-Entrance Test. National Testing Agency shall be the organization to conduct National Eligibility- cum-Entrance Test for admission to MBBS/BDS/BAMS/BUMS/BHMS courses. Accordingly, the National Testing Agency, Delhi conducted the National EligibilitY Cum Entrance Test for the session 2024-25.\r\n\r\n15% seats in Government, Corporation and Govt.-Aided Medical and Dental Colleges of Maharashtra will be filled by Directorate General of Health Services, New Delhi (DGHS) And 15% seats in Government / Govt.-Aided & Unaided Private/Minority Colleges of AYUSH courses in Maharashtra will be filled by AACCC on the basis of All India NEET Rank.\r\n\r\nThe Competent Authority shall issue Notice regarding schedule of online registration and submission of online Application from eligible candidates for the preparation of provisional state merit list for admission to undergraduate courses for all seats available with The Competent Authority in State of Maharashtra.', 'Eligibility\r\nEligibility For Admission To Health Science Degree Course\r\n\r\n•\r\nThe candidate must be an Indian National\r\n•\r\nThe candidate must be registered with State CET cell, Mumbai through online application on website of State CET Cell\r\n•\r\nDomicile of Candidate: The Candidates must be Domicile of Maharashtra\r\n•\r\nThe candidate must have passed the SSC or equivalent examination from an Institution situated in the state of Maharashtra\r\n•\r\nThe candidate must have passed the qualifying examination i.e. Higher Secondary\r\n•\r\nCertificate (HSC/12th Standard) or equivalent examination, from an Institution situated in the State of Maharashtra exception) with English, Physics, Chemistry and Biology (Botany & Zoology) at the time of document verification\r\n\r\nEligibility criteria of Qualifying Examination for various courses\r\n\r\nFor MBBS/BDS/BAMS/BUMS/BHMS\r\n\r\nOPEN Category and EWS Category	Category must have obtained not less than 50% marks in Physics, Chemistry and Biology taken together at the HSC\r\nconstitutional reservation and constitutional reservation with PWD	Must have obtained not less than 40% (i.e. 120 out of 300) marks in Physics, Chemistry and Biology taken together at the HSC (or equivalent) Examination\r\n\r\n\r\nFor BPTh, BOTh, BASLP & BP & O CourseS\r\n\r\nPassing grade at HSC/12th Standard or equivalent examination is however necessary\r\n\r\nFor admission to BP&O\r\n\r\nCandidates who have passed 12th standard examination with Physics, Chemistry, Biology and / or Mathematics are eligible\r\n\r\nFor admission to BASLP\r\n\r\nCandidates who have passed 12th standard examination with Physics, Biology, Chemistry and/or Mathematics and/or Computer Science are eligible', 'Reservation Policy\r\nCategory	Reservation %\r\nOPEN Category and EWS Category	Category must have obtained not less than 50% marks in Physics, Chemistry and Biology taken together at the HSC\r\nconstitutional reservation and constitutional reservation with PWD	Must have obtained not less than 40% (i.e. 120 out of 300) marks in Physics, Chemistry and Biology taken together at the HSC (or equivalent) Examination', 'Name of the Course	Candidate seeking admission for State Quota Seats	Candidate seeking admission for Institute Quota Seats	Candidate seeking admission for both State Quota and Institute Quota\r\nMBBS, BDS, BAMS, BHMS & BUMS	Rs. 1000/-	Rs. 5000/-	Rs. 6000/-\r\nBPTH, BOTH, BASLP & BP&O	Rs. 1000/-	Rs. 1000/-	Rs. 1000/-', 'Process Flow\r\nFlowchart\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nOnline registration\r\n\r\nApplication form filling\r\n\r\nPayment of registration fees\r\n\r\nUploading of Documents\r\n\r\nPublication of State Merit list\r\n\r\n\r\nRound 1\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nOnline preferences(choices) filling process for first round\r\n\r\nDeclaration of the list of selected candidates of the first round\r\n\r\nLast date of joining to the respective college for the first round\r\n\r\n\r\nRound 2\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nOnline preferences(choices) filling process for second round\r\n\r\nDeclaration of the list of selected candidates of the second round\r\n\r\nLast date of joining to the respective college for the second round\r\n\r\n\r\nRound 3\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nOnline registration, application form filling, payment of registration fees and uploading of Documents for Round 3 (if not registered previously)\r\n\r\nPublication of Combined State Merit list (Round 1 &Round 3 )\r\n\r\nOnline preferences(choices) filling process for Round 3\r\n•\r\nDeclaration of the list of selected candidate for Round 3\r\n\r\nLast date of joining to the respective colleges for Round 3\r\n\r\n\r\nOnline Stray Vacancy round(s)\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nCut-off-date of admission process for MBBS\r\n\r\nCut-off-date of admission process for BDS', 'FAQ\r\nCan I Do MBBS Without NEET ?\r\nNo, it\'s not possible to do MBBS without NEET. Candidates must have to appear for the NEET exam for admissions. However, there are only a few private colleges in India that offer direct MBBS admissions or through any other entrance test.\r\n\r\nWhat is the age limit for NEET?\r\nThe age limit for NEET is 17 years. Candidates appearing for the NEET exam must be older than 17 years while registering for the NEET exam.\r\n\r\nHow many government MBBS seats are available in Maharashtra?\r\nThere are 4825 Government MBBS Seats Availible in Maharashtra\r\n\r\nWhat is required to satisfy eligibility criteria as far as only 12th Std. is concerned? Is it 50% marks in PCB or 50% in PCBE or 50% in grand total?\r\nGeneral category: A candidate must have passed in the subjects of Physics, Chemistry, Biology/Bio-technology and English individually and must have obtained a minimum of 50% marks taken together in Physics, Chemistry, Biology/Biotechnology at the Qualifying Examination.\r\n\r\nSC, ST and OBC-NCL category: The marks obtained in Physics, Chemistry, Biology/Biotechnology taken in qualifying examination must be 40% marks.\r\n\r\nFor candidates with Benchmark Disabilities: the minimum marks in qualifying examination in Physics, Chemistry and Biology/Biotechnology taken together must be 45%.\r\n\r\nIs there any restriction for filling up number of choices of Institution (College) in choice filling form?\r\nNo, you can give as many choices as you wish during online choice filling.\r\n\r\nWhat Documents Are Required For Admission process?\r\n•\r\nAdmit card of NEET UG 2023\r\n•\r\nCopy of Online Application Form (Latest) filled on www.mahacet.org\r\n•\r\nNEET-UG 2023 Mark sheet\r\n•\r\nNationality certificate issued by District Magistrate/Addl. District Magistrate or Metropolitan Magistrate / valid Indian passport /School Leaving Certificate of HSC/12th Std. indicating the nationality of the candidate as Indian\r\n•\r\nDomicile Certificate issued by District Magistrate/Metropolitan Magistrate/ Addl. District Magistrate or Competent Authority for issue of such certificate\r\n•\r\nH.S.C. (or equivalent) examination marksheet\r\n•\r\nSSC (or equivalent) passing certificate (for Date of Birth)\r\n•\r\nAadhar Card\r\n•\r\nMedical fitness certificate (Annexure - H)\r\n\r\nIf Applicable :\r\n\r\n\r\n•\r\nCaste Certificate\r\n•\r\nCaste Validity Certificate\r\n•\r\nNon Creamy layer Certificate valid upto 31/03/2025 (For DT-A, NT-B, NT-C, NT-D& OBC including SBC)\r\n•\r\nEx-servicemen Certificate /actual service certificate\r\n•\r\nDomicile of Maharashtra Certificate of Defence person\r\n•\r\nTransfer certificate and Domicile of other than Maharashtra certificate of parents\r\n•\r\nEligibility Certificate for EWS category issued by appropriate authority, for the year 2024-25\r\n•\r\nMKB: Disputed area certificate, Mother tongue certificate, SSC/HSC from MKB area\r\n•\r\nHA: Parent Domicile certificate, SSC/HSC of candidate from hilly area\r\n•\r\nFor Person with disability (PWD) Candidates - Medical Fitness Certificate of Authorized Medical Board\r\n•\r\nFor Minority Candidates - Refer rule 5.11, 5.12 & 5.13\r\n•\r\nFor Orphan - respective certificate from Women and Child welfare department\r\nWhich Candidates are eligible for seat allotment in Round 2 ? Que -Which Candidates are eligible for seat allotment in Round 2 ?\r\n•\r\nRegistered candidates who did not fill choices in Round 1\r\n•\r\nRegistered candidates who participated in Round1 but did not get any seat allotted in Round 1\r\n•\r\nRegistered candidates, whose seat allotted in Round 1 got cancelled during the document verification\r\n•\r\nCandidates who have reported/joined at allotted institute during the joining period of Round1 of allotment and did not filled Status Retention Form\r\n•\r\nCandidate who does not join the allotted seat during Round1\r\n•\r\nCandidate who has joined and resigned upto the last date of joining Round 1\r\nCandidate who has joined and resigned upto the last date of joining Round 1.\r\n•\r\nRegistered candidates who did not fill choices in Round1 & Round 2\r\n•\r\nCandidates who are joined in Round 2 but did not filled Status Rentension Form\r\n•\r\nRegistered candidates who participated in Round1 & Round2 but did not get any seat allotted in Round1 & Round2\r\n•\r\nCandidates who have registered in Round 3\r\nEligible Which Candidates Are Eligible For Online CAP Stray Vacancy Round ?\r\nCandidate who have registered & filled online preference form previously but not been allotted a seat till Round 3.', NULL, 2, 1, '2026-01-08 09:53:46', '2026-01-08 11:00:50'),
(62, 'PG', 2, 'Graduate Record Examination', 'Graduate Record Examination', './assets/images/gre.png', 'Graduate_Record_Examination', 'The Graduate Record Examination (GRE) is a standardized international test used for admissions to graduate and doctoral programs in universities worldwide, especially in the United States and other English-speaking countries. It measures a candidate’s verbal reasoning, quantitative reasoning, critical thinking, and analytical writing skills.\r\n\r\nThe GRE is widely accepted for Master’s and PhD programs in fields such as engineering, science, business, social sciences, and humanities. Some institutions also consider GRE scores for fellowships and assistantships.\r\n\r\nKey Highlights:\r\n\r\nAdministered by ETS (Educational Testing Service).\r\n\r\nAvailable as computer-based test (CBT) or paper-based test in selected regions.\r\n\r\nScores are valid for 5 years from the test date.\r\n\r\nIncludes three sections: Verbal Reasoning, Quantitative Reasoning, and Analytical Writing.', 'Educational Qualification:\r\n\r\nThere is no specific degree requirement to appear for GRE.\r\n\r\nCandidates typically applying for Master’s, PhD, or other graduate programs can take the exam.\r\n\r\nMost test-takers have a bachelor’s degree or are in the final year of undergraduate studies.\r\n\r\nAge Limit:\r\n\r\nNo age limit. Candidates of any age can take the GRE.\r\n\r\nNationality:\r\n\r\nOpen to all nationalities; both Indian and international students can apply.\r\n\r\nOther Requirements:\r\n\r\nMust have a valid identification document (passport, national ID, etc.) for registration and test-day verification.\r\n\r\nNo restrictions on the number of times you can appear for the exam (up to ETS rules: once every 21 days, maximum 5 times in a year).', 'Category / Reservation Type       Details                                      SC (Scheduled Caste)               No reservation; same fee and process for all ', 'Candidate Category                                   Fee (USD) Approx. Fee (INR)  Notes                                 \r\nAll Candidates (General/SC/ST/OBC/NRI/International) 230        ~19,000           Standard GRE General Test Fee              \r\nGRE Subject Test Fee                                 150        ~12,500           Optional subject-specific test             \r\n Additional Score Report                               27        ~2,200             Sending scores to more than 4 institutions \r\n Rescheduling Fee                                     50         ~4,200            If test date is changed                    Fee                                     50        ~4,200             Non-refundable                             \r\n Late Registration Fee                                25         ~2,100             If registering after deadline              \r\n', 'GRE – Process Flow\r\n\r\nCreate ETS Account\r\n\r\nRegister on the ETS official website and create a profile.\r\n\r\nChoose Test Type & Date\r\n\r\nSelect either the GRE General Test or GRE Subject Test.\r\n\r\nPick a suitable test center and date (computer-based or paper-based).\r\n\r\nPay Exam Fee\r\n\r\nPay the standard GRE fee online using credit/debit card or other accepted payment methods.\r\n\r\nPrepare for the Exam\r\n\r\nStudy Verbal Reasoning, Quantitative Reasoning, and Analytical Writing for the General Test.\r\n\r\nPrepare the subject-specific syllabus if taking the GRE Subject Test.\r\n\r\nTake the Test\r\n\r\nAppear at the test center on the scheduled date and complete the exam.\r\n\r\nEnsure valid identification is carried to the center.\r\n\r\nReceive Scores\r\n\r\nGRE scores are typically available 10–15 days after the test.\r\n\r\nScores can be sent to universities directly through ETS.\r\n\r\nApply to Universities\r\n\r\nUse GRE scores to apply for graduate or doctoral programs worldwide.\r\n\r\nSome universities may have additional requirements (interviews, SOP, recommendation letters).\r\n\r\nRetake (Optional)\r\n\r\nIf desired, the GRE can be retaken. ETS allows up to 5 attempts in a year, with 21 days between attempts.', 'FAQs about Maharashtra Medical NEET PG admission process.', NULL, 1, 1, '2026-01-08 09:53:46', '2026-01-09 07:43:14'),
(64, 'PG', 1, 'all-india-ayush-neet-pg', 'All India Ayush Process NEET PG (AIAP PG)', './assets/images/AACCC.jpeg', 'All India Ayush Admission Process', 'Introduction\r\nAyush Admissions Central Counselling Committee (AACCC) of the Ministry of Ayush, Govt. of India, New Delhi is conducting Online Counselling for the allotment of AIQ-Post Graduate (MD/MS) seats of Ayurveda /Siddha /Unani /Homoeopathy under Govt. /Govt. Aided /Central Universities /National Institutes /Deemed Universities (100%) and Institutional seats of BHU to AIAPGET qualified eligible candidates since 2019. The allotment of seats to the candidates is made based on the AIAPGET 2023, Examination conducted by the National Testing Agency (NTA).', 'Eligibility\r\nAll candidates qualified for the AIAPGET - 2023 Examination are eligible.\r\n\r\nQuota Distribution\r\n\r\n15% All India Quota PG (MD/MS) Seats of Govt./Govt. aided institute of all States/UTs\r\n\r\n100% PG (AIQ and Institutional Quota) Ayurveda Seats of BHU, Varanasi, Uttar Pradesh\r\n\r\n100% PG (Ayurved) seats of ITRA, Jamnagar, Gujarat (except nominated seats)\r\n\r\n50% PG (Ayurved) seats of NIA, Jaipur, Rajasthan (except nominated seats)\r\n\r\n50% PG (Ayurved) seats of AIIA, Goa\r\n\r\n100% PG (Homoeopathy) seats of NIH, Kolkata, West Bengal (except nominated seats)\r\n\r\n100% PG (Homoeopathy) seats of NIH, Narela, Delhi\r\n\r\n100% PG (Homoeopathy) seats of NHRIMH, Kottayam, Kerala\r\n\r\n100% PG (Unani) seats of NIUM, Bangalore, Karnataka (except nominated seats)\r\n\r\n100% PG (Unani) seats of NRIUMSD, Hyderabad, Telangana (except nominated seats)\r\n\r\n100% PG (Unani) seats of RRIUM, Srinagar, Kashmir (except nominated seats)\r\n\r\n50% PG (Unani) seats of AMU, Aligarh, Uttar Pradesh\r\n\r\n50% PG (Siddha) seats of NIS, Chennai, Tamil Nadu\r\n\r\n100% PG-AU&H seats of all Deemed Universities', 'Reservation Policy\r\nCategory	Reservation Percentage\r\nSchedule Caste and Schedule Caste converted to Buddhism (SC)	15%\r\nSchedule Tribe (ST)	7.5%\r\nOther Backward Category (OBC) Including SBC	27%\r\nEWS	10%\r\nPerson with Disability (PwD)	5%', 'Fee Structure\r\nCategory	NEET PG counselling fee	Security deposit\r\nCentral university General category candidates AIQ	Rs. 2000/-	Rs. 10000/-\r\nSC/ ST/ OBC/ PwD category candidates	Rs. 1000/-	Rs. 10000/-', '1. Qualify NEET PG → 2. Register online on AIAP portal → 3. Document verification → 4. Choice filling → 5. Seat allotment → 6. Reporting to allotted college → 7. Mop-up/Stray vacancy rounds if applicable.', 'FAQ\r\nHow do I register on the AACCC website/Portal, and how do I fill in Choices?\r\nCandidates must log on to the website (www.aaccc.gov.in) to register and fill in choices. Before choice filling/locking for each round, candidates are advised to make a tentative list of colleges or courses as per preference after going through the provisional seat matrix uploaded in the \"Current events\" section of the AACCC website.\r\n\r\nHow and when do I have to make the payment for AACCC-PG counseling?\r\nAfter registration, the payment page appears automatically. Candidates can only make online payments by Net Banking /Credit card/ Debit card. After the successful completion of payment, the candidate can proceed with choice filling.', NULL, 1, 1, '2026-01-08 10:26:38', '2026-01-08 10:28:52');

